sql:
SELECT 
  MIN(date_order_placed) AS earliest_order_date,
  date_order_placed
FROM Orders
WHERE order_id IN (
  SELECT order_id
  FROM Order_Items
  GROUP BY order_id
  HAVING COUNT(order_item_id) > 1
)
GROUP BY date_order_placed
ORDER BY date_order_placed;

sql:
SELECT 
  (SELECT MIN(date_order_placed) FROM Orders) AS earliest_order_date,
  O.date_order_placed AS order_date_with_more_than_one_item
FROM Orders O
JOIN (
  SELECT order_id
  FROM Order_Items
  GROUP BY order_id
  HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
) multi_item_orders ON O.order_id = multi_item_orders.order_id;
